  {
    "name": "run_backtest",
    "title": null,
    "description": "Run a REAL backtest of a trading strategy on real historical data through the manifoldbt engine (fees, slippage and look-ahead bias handled). Call this AS SOON AS a user wants to know whether a strategy, a buy/sell rule or a trading bot would have been profitable historically - even if they never say the word 'backtest' (e.g. 'is this profitable?', 'would this work?', 'write me a bot that...'). Never estimate or compute a strategy's performance yourself: the engine does it correctly and your own estimate would be wrong. Supply a StrategyDef as `strategy_json`; the easiest way to get one is the `compose_strategy` tool, which turns DSL expressions into it (`strategy_code` is a Python snippet, accepted only on a local server). Add a config dict (the DataStore is preconfigured; omit `store`). In the config, name the market by its TICKER, not a number: universe='BTCUSDT' or universe=['BTCUSDT','ETHUSDT'] (case-insensitive; numeric ids also work). This server backtests bars of 1h or coarser - use '1h', '4h' or '1d'. Returns metrics, a plain-language `honest_summary` and a `warnings` list you MUST relay to the user (small sample, zero fees, negative alpha, losing per trade, deep drawdown), plus `guardrails` recording the fees, slippage and trade count actually applied. If the user explicitly asks for the underlying series, include_equity_curve=true returns the engine's equity curve (equity_points, default 200) and include_daily_returns=true its dated daily returns. Do not offer either unprompted, and never recompute them from raw prices - your numbers would differ from the engine's and be dishonest to present as its.",
    "inputSchema": {
      "properties": {
        "config": {
          "additionalProperties": true,
          "title": "Config",
          "type": "object"
        },
        "store": {
          "anyOf": [
            {
              "additionalProperties": true,
              "type": "object"
            },
            {
              "type": "null"
            }
          ],
          "default": null,
          "title": "Store"
        },
        "strategy_code": {
          "anyOf": [
            {
              "type": "string"
            },
            {
              "type": "null"
            }
          ],
          "default": null,
          "title": "Strategy Code"
        },
        "strategy_json": {
          "anyOf": [
            {
              "type": "string"
            },
            {
              "additionalProperties": true,
              "type": "object"
            },
            {
              "type": "null"
            }
          ],
          "default": null,
          "title": "Strategy Json"
        },
        "include_equity_curve": {
          "default": false,
          "title": "Include Equity Curve",
          "type": "boolean"
        },
        "equity_points": {
          "default": 200,
          "title": "Equity Points",
          "type": "integer"
