  {
    "name": "run_sweep",
    "title": null,
    "description": "Sweep a strategy's parameters over a Cartesian grid. Call this whenever a user wants 'the best value' of a parameter, wants to 'optimise', 'tune' or 'improve' a strategy, or wants to test a range - do not guess good parameter values yourself. A high best raw Sharpe picked out of many combinations is almost always overfitting, not a real edge: tell the user the winner was selected out of N combinations, prefer a stable RANGE over a single point, and re-run the top combo through run_backtest for an exact P&L before trusting it. param_grid maps parameter names (declared via param('name') in the strategy) to lists of values; each returned row carries the 'params' that produced it. The default lite path derives cagr, calmar and ulcer_index from one equity point per UTC day, so those three differ slightly from run(); every other metric matches it exactly. Returns an `overfitting_correction` you MUST relay: never present the best raw Sharpe without it. Its `probability_edge_is_real` is the Deflated Sharpe Ratio - a PROBABILITY between 0 and 1 that the winner is a real edge rather than selection noise across the N combinations tried. It is NOT a corrected Sharpe value: report it as a probability (e.g. '91% chance this is real'), never as 'a Sharpe of 0.91'. `expected_max_sharpe_under_null` is the best Sharpe pure noise alone would be expected to produce over that many tries.",
    "inputSchema": {
      "properties": {
        "param_grid": {
          "additionalProperties": {
            "items": {},
            "type": "array"
          },
          "title": "Param Grid",
          "type": "object"
        },
